    correct: 1,
    explanation: `$\\sum F_y = 0 \\rightarrow N_g = 10 \\text{ N}$. $\\sum F_x = 0 \\rightarrow f_g = R_w$.\nMoments about foot: $R_w(L\\cos 30^\\circ) = 10(L/2 \\sin 30^\\circ) \\rightarrow R_w = \\frac{5 \\sin 30^\\circ}{\\cos 30^\\circ} = 5\\tan 30^\\circ = 2.887 \\text{ N}$.\n$\\mu = f_g/N_g = 2.887/10 = 0.289$.`
