    correct: 2,
    explanation: `As $\\theta$ increases, $\\cos\\theta$ decreases ($N$ falls) while $\\sin\\theta$ increases ($f$ rises). Slipping begins when $mg \\sin\\theta = \\mu_s mg \\cos\\theta$, giving critical angle $\\tan\\theta_c = \\mu_s$.`
