    explanation: `Let $AC = x$. Apply $\\sum \\tau = 0$ about B: $R_A \\times 1 = 500 \\times (1 - x)$.\nWhen A is at maximum limit, $300 = 500(1 - x) \\rightarrow 1 - x = 0.6 \\rightarrow x = 0.4 \\text{ m}$.`
