    q: `A book rests on a table. The weight of the book acts downward and the normal force acts upward — they are equal in magnitude and opposite in direction. Are they a Newton's Third Law pair?`,
    options:[`Yes, because they are equal and opposite`, `No, because they both act on the same body (the book)`, `Yes, because they are contact forces`, `No, because they are different magnitudes`],
    correct: 1,
